<cell alignment="center" valignment="top" usebox="none">
\begin_inset Text

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\series bold
\color blue
EMRI surrogate modeling and late time Kerr tails with spinning primary Black
 Hole using discontinuous Galerkin method
\color inherit

\begin_inset Newline linebreak
\end_inset


\size small
Dr.
 Scott Field and Dr.
 Gaurav Khanna, UMass Dartmouth
\series default
\size default

\begin_inset Newline linebreak
\end_inset

It is need of the hour to have a gravitational wave template bank for upcoming
 detectors.
 This project deals with one of the primary sources of the upcoming space
 borne detector LISA which are extreme mass ratio black hole binaries.
 I have written a very accurate Teukolsky solver code using discontinuous
 Galerkin method to model the waveform from EMRI system with a spinning
 primary.
\begin_inset Newline linebreak
\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset
</cell>
</row>
<row>
<cell alignment="left" valignment="top" usebox="none">
\begin_inset Text

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\color cyan
June 27, 2020 - June 2021 
\series bold
\color blue
(MS project)
\end_layout

\end_inset
</cell>
<cell alignment="left" valignment="top" usebox="none">
\begin_inset Text

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\noindent

\series bold
\color blue
Massless Scalar Waves in AdS Spacetime
\color inherit
 
\begin_inset Newline linebreak
\end_inset


\size small
Dr.
 Rajesh Nayak, IISER Kolkata
\series default
\size default

\begin_inset Newline linebreak
\end_inset

It has been shown in recent works that the non-asymptotic AdS spacetime
 eventually loses the curvature due to the formation of a black hole.
 The boundary conditions for this system are complicated, and hence very
 little work has been done on this topic computationally.
 I intend to explore the stability of the AdS spacetime when perturbed by
 gravitational waves.
 I am using the scalar perturbations to study the solution of the massless
 scalar wave equation in this geometry.
 I have started working on 4-dimensional spacetimes, but it can be extended
 to N-dimensions.
\begin_inset Newline linebreak
\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset
</cell>
</row>
<row>
<cell alignment="left" valignment="top" usebox="none">
\begin_inset Text

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\color cyan
Aug.
 2020 - Dec.
 2020
\end_layout

\end_inset
</cell>
<cell alignment="left" valignment="top" usebox="none">
\begin_inset Text

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\series bold
\color blue
Independent study on Magnetohydrodynamics (MHD) and Fluid Dynamics
\color inherit
 
\begin_inset Newline linebreak
\end_inset


\size small
Dr.
 Dibyendu Nandi, IISER Kolkata
\series default
\size default

\begin_inset Newline linebreak
\end_inset

The motivation for this independent study comes from General Relativistic
 Magnetohydrodynamic simulation of Neutron Stars.
 I aim to teach myself the concepts of Advection Equation and different
 types of flows in fluid systems.
 I am acquiring skills in MHD simulations so that I could learn the techniques
 of General Relativistic version of it.
 
